<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Trinchese" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[274,405,1567,1590]" class="Gastropoda" family="Limapontiidae" genus="Placida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="31" pageNumber="296" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tardyi">
<emphasis box="[274,405,1567,1590]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="296">Placida tardyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (f) 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Trinchese" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[445,576,1567,1590]" class="Gastropoda" family="Limapontiidae" genus="Placida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="31" pageNumber="296" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis box="[445,576,1567,1590]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="296">Placida viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (g) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1901" box="[623,730,1567,1590]" class="Gastropoda" family="Plakobranchidae" genus="Elysia" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="31" pageNumber="296" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="flava">
<emphasis box="[623,730,1567,1590]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="296">Elysia flava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1827" box="[742,879,1567,1590]" class="Gastropoda" family="Siphonariidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonariida" pageId="31" pageNumber="296" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Siphonariidae</taxonomicName>
: (h) 
<taxonomicName box="[923,1094,1567,1590]" class="Gastropoda" family="Siphonariidae" genus="Williamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonariida" pageId="31" pageNumber="296" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gussoni">Williamia gussoni</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="32.[160,1156,142,341]" box="[160,409,142,168]" pageId="32" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,409,142,168]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="297">External morphology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[160,1156,142,341]" pageId="32" pageNumber="297">Body elongate, narrow, background colour red and semi-transparent, with dispersed white dots concentrated around head, cerata and rhinophore apexes. Cerata globular, leaf-shaped, semi-transparent, with internal lines of red colour running towards apex and surrounded by four tubercles. Rhinophores beige, internally rolled, bifid with superior apex slightly longer than inferior one.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="297" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="32.[160,1155,395,525]" box="[160,252,395,421]" pageId="32" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,252,395,421]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="297">Ecology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[160,1155,395,525]" pageId="32" pageNumber="297">
Specimens were found on the red alga 
<taxonomicName authority="(J. Agardh) Thuret, 1855" authorityName="Thuret" authorityYear="1855" baseAuthorityName="J. Agardh" box="[590,1077,430,455]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Ceramiaceae" genus="Bornetia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ceramiales" pageId="32" pageNumber="297" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="species" species="secundiflora">
<emphasis box="[590,814,430,455]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="297">Bornetia secundiflora</emphasis>
(J.Agardh) Thuret, 1855
</taxonomicName>
, where they were mating and laying the eggs. The egg mass is whitish, cylindrical and ‘C’-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[167,258,500,525]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="24.[160,225,1510,1533]" captionTargetBox="[166,1149,146,1476]" captionTargetId="figure-3@24.[163,1152,142,1479]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 5. Photographs of live Pteropoda species: (a) Creseis virgula. (b) Hyalocylis striata. (c) Peracle reticulata. (d) Pneumodermopsis canephora. Runcinida: (e) Runcina ornata. Sacoglossa: (f) Aplysiopsis elegans. (g) Caliphylla mediterránea. (h) Cyerce graeca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758448" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758448/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="297">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(b), close-up); they were laid under the algae, around 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thuret" authorityYear="1855" baseAuthorityName="J. Agardh" box="[848,1003,500,525]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Ceramiaceae" genus="Bornetia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ceramiales" pageId="32" pageNumber="297" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="species" species="secundiflora">
<emphasis box="[848,1003,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="297">B. secundiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but not on it.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="297" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="32.[160,1156,578,777]" box="[160,300,578,604]" pageId="32" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,300,578,604]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="297">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[160,1156,578,777]" pageId="32" pageNumber="297">
Central American coast and 
<collectingCountry box="[477,569,614,639]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="32" pageNumber="297">England</collectingCountry>
(iNaturalist.org 2021); 
<collectingCountry box="[824,919,614,639]" name="Portugal" pageId="32" pageNumber="297">Portugal</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cervera JL &amp; Calado G &amp; Gavaia C &amp; Malaquias MAE &amp; Templado J &amp; Ballesteros M &amp; Megina C &amp; Garcia-Gomez JC" box="[932,1142,614,639]" pageId="32" pageNumber="297" pagination="5 - 111" refId="ref18631" refString="Cervera JL, Calado G, Gavaia C, Malaquias MAE, Templado J, Ballesteros M, Megina C, Garcia-Gomez JC. 2004. An annotated and updated checklist of the opisthobranchs (Mollusca: Gastropoda) from Spain and Portugal (including Islands and archipelagos). Boletin-Instituto Espanol de Oceanografia. 20: 5 - 111." type="journal article" year="2004">Cervera et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingCountry box="[160,257,648,673]" name="Gibraltar" pageId="32" pageNumber="297">Gibraltar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Garcia-Gomez JC" box="[269,489,648,673]" pageId="32" pageNumber="297" pagination="397" refId="ref19702" refString="Garcia-Gomez JC. 2002. Paradigmas de una fauna insolita. Los moluscos opistobranquios del estrecho de Gibraltar (Serie Ciencias). Inst Estudios Gibraltarenos. 20: 397." type="journal article" year="2002">García-Gómez 2002</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingCountry box="[508,573,648,673]" name="Spain" pageId="32" pageNumber="297">Spain</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[582,656,648,673]" country="Spain" name="Galicia" pageId="32" pageNumber="297">Galicia</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rolan E" box="[667,793,648,673]" pageId="32" pageNumber="297" refId="ref22127" refString="Rolan E. 1983. Moluscos de la Ria de Vigo. I. Gasteropodos. Santiago de Compostela (La Coruna, Spain): Universidad de Santiago, Colegio Universitario de Vigo. 383." type="book" year="1983">Rolán 1983</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingRegion box="[812,923,648,673]" country="Spain" name="Andalucia" pageId="32" pageNumber="297">Andalucía</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cervera JL &amp; Garcia-Gomez JC &amp; Ortea J" box="[935,1142,648,673]" pageId="32" pageNumber="297" pagination="215 - 224" refId="ref18719" refString="Cervera JL, Garcia-Gomez JC, Ortea J. 1988. Una nueva especie del genero Hermaea (Gastropoda: Opisthobranchia: Sacoglossa) y redescripcion de dos raros sacoglosos de la malacofauna europea. Iberus. 8: 215 - 224." type="journal article" year="1988">Cervera et al. 1988</bibRefCitation>
